“Get these fucking chains off!” Rorge screamed. 
Gendry ignored them. “You go first, then her, then me. Hurry, it’s a long way.”...
text:
“Get these fucking chains off!” Rorge screamed.
Gendry ignored them. “You go first, then her, then me. Hurry, it’s a long way.”
“When you split the firewood,” Arya remembered, “where did you leave the axe?”
“Out by the haven.” He spared a glance for the chained men. “I’d save the donkeys first. There’s no time.”
“You take her!” she yelled. “You get her out! You do it!” The fire beat at her back with hot red wings as she fled the burning barn.

summary: Dear Game of Thrones Fandom,
body:
Dear Game of Thrones Fandom,

Please explain why the AO3 feed for Gendrya is mostly Jon x Sansa and Sandor x Sansa? With only a wee bit of Arya and Gendry in the background?

There so little Gendrya stuff to begin with, why fill up The feed with Sansa?

No this is not an anti sansa post. I just dont find her as interesting as Arya, Jon, Ygritte, Davos, Gendry, Brienne, Tyrion, Podrick, The Knight King, Sam, Gilly, Ned, Missendei, Greyworn, Danaerys. (My favorites)

While we’re on the subject, lets get some Missendei Greyworm fluff out there.

Why do so much of their fics focusnon the fact that Greyworm has no penis. Like, ya’ll can imagine Jon would want to fuck his sister. (Technically he was adopted so yeah) but cant imagine a universe where Greyworm has a dick?

Anyway, in short. More Gendrya, less, Other people in the Gendrya tag. And more Missandei and Greyworm.

tags: It makes sense in so many ways!
summary: Just read your Arya killing Dany post.  Intetesting! Sansa protecting him from the North via marriage and Arya protecting him...
question: Just read your Arya killing Dany post.  Intetesting! Sansa protecting him from the North via marriage and Arya protecting him from Dany.  Certainly plays into the protection theme.  First with what Ned did for Jon and now this.  Full circle. Full circle seems to be the theme of the series.  Basically what LF told Sansa.
answer:
Dear nonny,

exactly! It is Aegon and his sisters, but a far better variant! And the protection theme was heavily alluded to in the “crypts of Winterfell” teaser. It really makes the story go full circle, and it fits with several of the foreshadowings in book and show. Arya killing someone not on her list, Arya killing the Queen, Arya killing someone who threatens her family, making up for her inability to save Robb. It is beautiful on so many levels.

I would also alert you to the addition to my post by @une-nuit-pour-se-souvenir who connected the F&B tidbit to a scene from AGOT.

And I must admit that I have the feeling that I finally understand where Arya’s arc is headed.

summary: Casual reminder - arya has never said she doesn’t want to get married or have children. She basically adopts Weasel. She openly...
body:
Casual reminder - arya has never said she doesn’t want to get married or have children. She basically adopts Weasel. She openly checks Gendry out, and thinks of him in romantic ways multiple times without realising it- she’s definitely gonna be up for romance when she’s older (If she processes and deals with the Raff incident… and learns that kisses and groping can be good. Arya bby, he didn’t care about anyone’s pleasure but his own, i’m so glad you killed him for multiple reasons.)

Arya doesn’t hate dresses themselves, she hates that she can’t run in them, because they’re impractical for that. All she wears in Essos are dresses and long tunics and breeches. All she wore in Winterfell growing up? Dresses. Give her a dress she can run in, and water dance with, and she’ll gladly wear it. Practical dresses, she’s down for. She’s wearing long tunics and breeches in essos- that’s something flowing at her knees, and breeches covering her legs. She can run in that shit, she’s quite content. 

Arya doesn’t reject being a lady bc she wants to be a knight- she doesn’t want to be a knight. That’s Bran’s dream. She doesn’t want to be a lady, because the idea of a lady that’s sold to her is being like her sister. She rejects the sexism that wants to restrict her because of how she was born. She can be a great “Lady” Lord of a castle, or a village, or an entire kingdom, but she will not be held down by the sexism of her world, and it’s idea of a demure good at stitching Lady

All she wore in Winterfell growing up? Dresses. Give her a dress she can run in, and water dance with, and she’ll gladly wear it. Practical dresses, she’s down for. She’s wearing long tunics and breeches in essos- that’s something flowing at her knees, and breeches covering her legs. She can run in that shit, she’s quite content. 

Arya doesn’t reject being a lady bc she wants to be a knight- she doesn’t want to be a knight. That’s Bran’s dream. She doesn’t want to be a lady, because the idea of a lady that’s sold to her is being like her sister. She rejects the sexism that wants to restrict her because of how she was born.
